==Chinese==
===Mandarin===
[[Pinyin]]: dŭzi lĭ de huíchóng
===Etymology===
Literally: (to know what a person is thinking as if one were) a ringworm inside (that person's) stomach
===Idiom===
# a mind reader; to read someone's mind
#: ''[[莉]][[经常]][[说]][[辉]][[是]][[她]]'''肚子里的蛔虫'''，[[好多]][[的]][[事情]][[都]][[不用]][[说]]，[[也]][[就是]][[心照不宣]][[吧]]。''[http://64.233.167.104/search?q=cache:HVIrWKEcL6cJ:www.chineseliterature.com.cn/qingsong/qing/001.htm+%22%E8%82%9A%E5%AD%90%E9%87%8C%E7%9A%84%E8%9B%94%E8%99%AB%22+site:.cn&hl=zh-CN&gl=cn&ct=clnk&cd=5]
#: ''Li often said that Hui could '''read her mind''', there were many things that were implicitly understood without needing to be said out loud.''
